.TH XRDGSITEST 1 "2026-07-06" "brix client" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
xrdgsitest \- probe GSI authentication against an XRootD endpoint
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B xrdgsitest
[\fIOPTS\fR] \fBroot\fR[\fBs\fR]\fB://\fR\fIhost\fR[\fI:port\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B xrdgsitest
forces GSI authentication and reports whether the handshake authenticated
successfully against the given XRootD endpoint.
It exits 0 on success, non-zero on any failure.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-tls
Require in-protocol TLS.
.TP
.B \-\-notlsok
Permit cleartext if the server offers no TLS.
.TP
.B \-\-noverifyhost
Skip TLS hostname verification (certificate chain check remains on).
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version and exit.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B X509_USER_PROXY
Path to the GSI proxy certificate.
.TP
.B X509_CERT_DIR
Directory containing trusted CA certificates.
.TP
.B XRDRC
Path to configuration file (default \fI~/.xrdrc\fR).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.xrdrc
Per-user configuration: endpoint aliases and default credentials.
See
.BR brix\-env (7).
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on successful GSI authentication.
50 on a usage error.
51 on a socket/connect/timeout error.
53 on an authentication failure.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR xrdcp (1),
.BR xrdgsiproxy (1),
.BR brix\-env (7)
